# 99 Rule Authoring and Change Control

## Intent
Keep the compliance rule system modular, stable, and auditable as the product evolves.

## Mandatory
- Every rule change must include rationale, scope impact, and effective date.
- Changes weakening controls require explicit risk acceptance record and approver.
- Keep rules atomic: one concern per file, linked from `index.mdc`.
- Preserve backward compatibility notes for active services/plugins.

## Versioning
- Use semantic version labels in change notes (major/minor/patch impact).
- Record superseded rules and migration guidance.

## Review Cadence
- Perform quarterly rule review for legal/regulatory drift.
- Trigger out-of-cycle review after major incidents or regulatory updates.
